b'[<p><i><b>UFC on Fox: Johnson vs. Reis</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC on Fox 24</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event produced by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> held on April 15, 2017, at the <a href="/wiki/Sprint_Center" title="Sprint Center">Sprint Center</a> in <a href="/wiki/Kansas_City,_Missouri" title="Kansas City, Missouri">Kansas City, Missouri</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-KCFN_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-KCFN-2">[2]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2017schedule_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-2017schedule-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was the first that the UFC has hosted in the state of <a href="/wiki/Missouri" title="Missouri">Missouri</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Kansas_City_metropolitan_area" title="Kansas City metropolitan area">Kansas City metropolitan area</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-KCFN_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-KCFN-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Flyweight_Championship" title="UFC Flyweight Championship">UFC Flyweight Championship</a> match between current champion <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Demetrious_Johnson_(fighter)" title="Demetrious Johnson (fighter)">Demetrious Johnson</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wilson_Reis" title="Wilson Reis">Wilson Reis</a> headlined this event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup> The pairing was originally booked for <a href="/wiki/UFC_201" title="UFC 201">UFC 201</a>, but Johnson pulled out due to an undisclosed injury and the bout was scrapped.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>UFC officials were initially targeting a featherweight bout between former <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/UFC_Bantamweight_Championship" title="UFC Bantamweight Championship">UFC Bantamweight Champion</a> <a href="/wiki/Renan_Bar%C3%A3o" title="Renan Bar\xc3\xa3o">Renan Bar\xc3\xa3o</a> and <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Doo_Ho_Choi" title="Doo Ho Choi">Doo Ho Choi</a> to serve as the event headliner.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup> However, as the announcement of the pairing began to circulate, Choi declined the bout, and as a result, Barao was rescheduled against a different opponent at another event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>With his win, Johnson tied <a href="/wiki/Anderson_Silva" title="Anderson Silva">Anderson Silva</a>\'s record for most consecutive title defenses (10).<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>]'